    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 2000, 4000, 8000 - CAB ACCESSORIES - TROUBLESHOOTING - Electric
        Windshield Washer, With Signal-Stat 910/915 Turn Signal Switch, With Truck With Mechanical Engines, and Air
        Brakes
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Electric Windshield Washer, With Signal-Stat 910/915 Turn Signal Switch, With Truck With Mechanical
            Engines, and Air Brakes
        </title>
        <table id="t0823220" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Electric Windshield Washer, With Signal-Stat 910/915 Turn Signal Switch, With Truck With Mechanical
                Engines, and Air Brakes
            </title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.85in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.79in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.86in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.32in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Check circuit breaker F18 for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>F18</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace circuit breaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Move key switch to ignition position and at F18 and circuit 12B measure voltage to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>F18, 12B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 12 or 12B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (31) and at circuit 82S measure voltage to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(31), 82S to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 82S, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Test wiper switch (31) by placing switch in off position and measuring resistance from
                                terminal 1 to 2.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Sw. (31), term. 1 to 2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Test wiper switch (31) by placing switch in low position and measuring resistance from
                                term. 2 to 3 and 4 to 5.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Sw. (31), term 2 to 3 and 4 to 5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Test wiper switch (31) by placing switch in high position and measuring resistance
                                from term. 5 to 6.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Sw. (31), term. 5 to 6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect switch (31) and disconnect conn. (29). Move key sw. to ignition position and
                                wiper sw. to low position and at conn. (29) circuit 82U, measure voltage to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(29), 82U to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 82U, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Move wiper switch to high position and at conn. (29) circuit 82T, measure voltage to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(29), 82T to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 82T, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At conn. (29), circuit 82B measure voltage to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(29), 82B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 82B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Move key switch and wiper switch to off position, and at conn. (29) measure resistance
                                from circuit 82U to 82V.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(29), 82U to 82V.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuits 82V or 82AB, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect wiper motor (29). Does wiper circuit function properly?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace wiper motor.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Does windshield washer function properly?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>End test.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>13.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect windshield washer switch (34) and at circuit 87K measure voltage to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(34), 87K to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 87K or 82, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>14.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Measure resistance across disconnected washer switch (34) while holding switch in the
                                on position.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Across switch (34).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace washer switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>15.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Is washer bottle mounted on left side?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 19.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>16.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect switch (34) and disconnect conn. (2). At (2) and circuit 87N measure voltage
                                to ground while an assistant closes switch (34).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(2), 87N to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 87P or 87N, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>17.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (2) and disconnect conn. (510). At (510) and circuit 87B measure
                                voltage to ground while an assistant closes switch (34).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(510), 87B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 87B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>18.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At conn. (510) measure voltage from circuit 87B to 11-GK while an assistant closes
                                switch (34).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(510), 87B to 11-GK.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 21.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 11-GK, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>19.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>On vehicles with washer bottle on right side of vehicle, reconnect switch (34) and
                                disconnect conn. (510). At (510) and circuit 87M measure voltage to ground while an
                                assistant closes switch (34).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(510), 87M to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 87M or 87P, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>20.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At conn. (510), measure voltage from circuit 87M to 87-G while an assistant closes
                                switch (34).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(510), 87M to 87-G.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 87-G or 11-GE, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>21.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect windshield washer pump conn. (510). Does windshield washer function
                                properly?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Windshield washer circuits check good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace washer pump.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
